<i>(RADIO ) They have no record of such
a brilliant display of astronomical pyrotechnics</i>

261
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:15,060
<i>ever taking place before.</i>

262
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:20,470
<i>Every country in the world has been able
to have a look at this unique phenomenon.</i>

263
00:21:20,640 --> 00:21:23,430
<i>As night has moved across the earth,</i>

264
00:21:23,600 --> 00:21:26,110
<i>the wonderful display has moved with it.</i>

265
00:21:26,280 --> 00:21:29,310
<i>Although the spectacle is losing its strength,</i>

266
00:21:29,480 --> 00:21:33,510
<i>the streets and parks and rooftops of London
are jammed with people</i>

267
00:21:33,680 --> 00:21:37,380
<i>watching one of the greatest entertainments
the world has ever...</i>

268
00:21:37,560 --> 00:21:39,350
(TURNS RADIO OFF)

269
00:21:40,320 --> 00:21:42,830
(WHITE NOISE)

270
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:39,510
<i>(TAPPING)</i>

271
00:23:43,640 --> 00:23:46,910
(KNOCKING)

272
00:23:47,080 --> 00:23:50,270
- Hello?
- Who's there?

273
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:53,510
My name's Mason. Bill Mason.

274
00:23:54,360 --> 00:23:58,550
- I'm in Room 22.
- Mason! I'm Dr Soames.

275
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:03,390
Of course. I should have recognised your voice.

276
00:24:03,560 --> 00:24:05,670
What's the matter?

277
00:24:05,840 --> 00:24:07,670
You can see?

278
00:24:07,840 --> 00:24:12,230
Nobody came to unbandage my eyes,
so I did it myself. No harm's been done.

279
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:16,510
- I can see as well as ever.
- I must telephone at once.

280
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:19,030
Where are we now?

281
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:21,830
- What do you mean?
- Where are we now?!

282
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:26,430
You've got eyes, dammit! Use them!
Can't you see I'm blind?

283
00:26:01,110 --> 00:26:06,470
<i>(RADIO ) Every country in the world has been
able to look at this unique phenomenon.</i>

284
00:26:06,630 --> 00:26:09,190
<i>As night has moved across the earth,</i>

285
00:26:09,350 --> 00:26:11,820
<i>the wonderful display has moved with it.</i>

286
00:26:11,990 --> 00:26:15,190
<i>Although the spectacle is losing its strength,</i>

287
00:26:15,350 --> 00:26:19,350
<i>the streets and parks and rooftops of London
are jammed with people</i>

288
00:26:19,510 --> 00:26:23,140
<i>watching one of the greatest entertainments
the world has ever...</i>

289
00:26:23,310 --> 00:26:24,750
(TURNS RADIO OFF)

290
00:27:13,830 --> 00:27:15,630
You can see?

291
00:27:15,790 --> 00:27:20,030
Nobody came to unbandage my eyes,
so I did it myself. No harm's been done.

292
00:27:20,190 --> 00:27:24,390
- I can see as well as ever.
- I must telephone at once.

293
00:27:24,550 --> 00:27:26,940
Where are we now?

294
00:27:27,110 --> 00:27:29,710
- What do you mean?
- Where are we now?!

295
00:27:29,870 --> 00:27:33,950
You've got eyes, dammit! Use them!
Can't you see I'm blind?

296
00:27:38,950 --> 00:27:42,260
It's useless. Dead.

297
00:27:43,190 --> 00:27:45,390
- You are still here?
- Yes.

298
00:27:49,390 --> 00:27:52,230
What are we going to do?

299
00:27:52,390 --> 00:27:56,070
I'll go and find help,
fetch another doctor. Stay here.

300
00:27:56,230 --> 00:27:59,540
- I shan't be long.
- You won't find anyone.

301
00:27:59,710 --> 00:28:02,710
Something terrible's happened.

302
00:28:02,870 --> 00:28:05,340
Very terrible.

303
00:28:07,070 --> 00:28:09,830
- Sister?
- (MAN) Who's there?

304
00:28:09,990 --> 00:28:12,790
- Is there a nurse about?
- No one's here.

305
00:28:12,950 --> 00:28:17,950
God knows what they're up to.
Draw the curtains, will you, mate?

306
00:28:21,750 --> 00:28:25,140
Don't muck about. Draw the bloody curtains.

307
00:28:45,270 --> 00:28:48,350
What the hell is happening?

308
00:29:00,070 --> 00:29:03,220
<i>(CALLS OF DESPERATION)</i>

309
00:29:21,270 --> 00:29:22,990
Doctor?

310
00:29:25,630 --> 00:29:27,990
Doctor Soames?

311
00:29:39,790 --> 00:29:41,860
(GIRL) Mummy!

312
00:29:42,030 --> 00:29:43,910
Mummy!

313
00:30:30,670 --> 00:30:34,270
(MAN) Keep close. Hang on.

314
00:30:34,430 --> 00:30:37,350
- What is it?
- I don't know. Ooh!

315
00:30:37,510 --> 00:30:40,590
It's a step. We're all right. It's a step.

316
00:30:40,750 --> 00:30:42,820
- Keep out on my left.
- Yes, OK.

317
00:30:42,990 --> 00:30:44,950
Not too far.

318
00:30:47,550 --> 00:30:49,510
(ENGINE MISSES)

319
00:30:58,550 --> 00:31:01,670
(ENGINE DIES)

320
00:31:02,910 --> 00:31:07,670
Did it stop? That was a car, wasn't it? Did it stop?

321
00:31:07,830 --> 00:31:12,030
Is anybody there? Can you see?

322
00:31:12,190 --> 00:31:15,630
Can someone see? Can you see?

323
00:31:16,990 --> 00:31:18,590
<i>Please...</i>

324
00:31:19,710 --> 00:31:22,430
<i>Please! Can you help us?</i>

325
00:31:22,590 --> 00:31:24,820
Excuse me, mate!

326
00:31:24,990 --> 00:31:28,510
Don't take no notice of these people.
They don't mean any harm.

327
00:31:28,670 --> 00:31:32,110
It's just that, well, I'm lost. We all are, here.

328
00:31:32,270 --> 00:31:37,830
<i>- Perhaps you can tell me where we are.
- I don't know. I've run out of petrol.</i>

329
00:31:37,990 --> 00:31:41,190
Well, could you show me
to the pavement, please?

330
00:31:48,030 --> 00:31:50,180
- You're staying with me.
- Let me go!

331
00:31:50,350 --> 00:31:52,790
I need a doctor. Daddy's gone blind!

332
00:31:52,950 --> 00:31:58,030
''Daddy's gone blind!'' We've all gone blind.
Only you haven't gone blind!

333
00:31:58,190 --> 00:32:01,150
- Let me go, please!
- Shut up!

334
00:32:01,310 --> 00:32:04,310
You're gonna be doing my seeing for me.

335
00:32:04,470 --> 00:32:08,590
First, you're gonna get me some food,
and some drink, right?

336
00:32:24,350 --> 00:32:27,070
<i>(CAR HORN BEEPS)</i>

337
00:32:36,230 --> 00:32:37,670
<i>(BEEP)</i>

338
00:32:39,750 --> 00:32:43,220
(CHILD IMITATES CAR ENGINE)

339
00:32:57,590 --> 00:33:00,270
Who is it? Who's there?!

340
00:33:01,350 --> 00:33:04,580
- Who is it, Tina?
- (BILL) She can see?

341
00:33:05,590 --> 00:33:10,910
- Don't you touch her! Leave her alone!
- It's all right! I don't wanna hurt her.

342
00:33:11,070 --> 00:33:16,070
I saw her in the street. I could tell she could see.
I don't mean any harm.

343
00:33:16,230 --> 00:33:19,070
- Can you see?
- Yeah.

344
00:33:19,230 --> 00:33:21,460
Oh, thank God!

345
00:33:22,750 --> 00:33:25,060
I told you, didn't I?

346
00:33:25,230 --> 00:33:29,700
Go and tell your mother.
Tell her other people can see. Go and tell her.

347
00:33:32,150 --> 00:33:35,990
We thought everyone had gone blind except her.

348
00:33:36,990 --> 00:33:40,270
There's no gas, no electric. Radio's gone.

349
00:33:40,430 --> 00:33:42,420
And the phone.

350
00:33:42,590 --> 00:33:45,950
When I woke up this morning, I couldn't see.

351
00:33:46,110 --> 00:33:48,550
My wife couldn't see, either. We thought...

352
00:33:49,190 --> 00:33:54,790
It's the same in all the other flats. There's been
people screaming and shouting for help.

353
00:33:54,950 --> 00:33:59,630
We thought it had happened
to the whole bloody world!

354
00:34:00,630 --> 00:34:03,750
You've been sent to help, have you?

355
00:34:06,390 --> 00:34:10,230
Say something for God's sake!
Tell us what's going on.

356
00:34:10,390 --> 00:34:13,390
I don't know what's going on.

357
00:34:13,550 --> 00:34:18,790
My eyes were bandaged. I took the bandages off
this morning, I found everything like this.

358
00:34:21,230 --> 00:34:23,380
Oh, Christ!

359
00:34:24,590 --> 00:34:28,430
You...didn't see the lights?

360
00:34:28,590 --> 00:34:30,070
Lights?

361
00:34:30,230 --> 00:34:33,460
- Last night. The comet lights.
- No.

362
00:34:33,630 --> 00:34:35,910
- John? John.
- Shirley.

363
00:34:36,070 --> 00:34:39,750
- I said stay in bed.
- Is there someone here who can see?

364
00:34:39,910 --> 00:34:42,830
- I said there would be.
- Can you really see?

365
00:34:42,990 --> 00:34:45,870
- Yeah, I can see.
- Have you come to help us?

366
00:34:46,030 --> 00:34:49,820
Of course he has. Now go back to bed, Shirley.

367
00:34:49,990 --> 00:34:54,150
She fell over in the bathroom this morning,
cracked her head.

368
00:34:54,310 --> 00:34:56,670
Sit down. Let me have a look.

369
00:34:56,830 --> 00:34:59,590
Oh, it's nothing, honestly.

370
00:34:59,750 --> 00:35:03,750
It's just the shock, I think. Tina bathed it for me.

371
00:35:03,910 --> 00:35:06,630
- (BILL) She's done a good job.
- It'll be fine.

372
00:35:08,310 --> 00:35:11,700
Why can't we see? What's happened to us?

373
00:35:11,870 --> 00:35:15,630
They're not sure yet.
They're still trying to find out.

374
00:35:15,790 --> 00:35:20,790
- How many people has it happened to?
- We're not sure about that either.

375
00:35:20,950 --> 00:35:24,740
It's just a limited area. They are sure about that.

376
00:35:24,910 --> 00:35:28,510
Our son's in France with the school
on an education trip.

377
00:35:28,670 --> 00:35:33,670
It might have been the comet lights.
She didn't see them and she's all right.

378
00:35:33,830 --> 00:35:36,300
The lights might have been too bright.

379
00:35:36,470 --> 00:35:40,430
(JOHN) It couldn't have been that.
They'd have warned us.

380
00:35:40,590 --> 00:35:43,060
Now go back to bed, Shirley.

381
00:35:43,230 --> 00:35:48,260
You might be concussed from that fall.
We can't risk you hurting yourself again.

382
00:35:48,430 --> 00:35:50,820
You go with her, Tina. Go on.

383
00:35:51,750 --> 00:35:55,110
I'm sure your husband's right.
Don't take any chances.

384
00:35:55,270 --> 00:35:57,340
No.

385
00:35:57,510 --> 00:35:59,820
Come on, darling.

386
00:36:01,990 --> 00:36:04,630
It's wonderful you're here.

387
00:36:09,750 --> 00:36:12,270
<i>(WHISPERS) Shut the door.</i>

388
00:36:18,950 --> 00:36:22,990
How many other people have you met
who can see?

389
00:36:23,990 --> 00:36:28,780
It's all right. I'm not telling Shirley.
I don't think she could cope knowing.

390
00:36:28,950 --> 00:36:33,390
But I've got to know because I've got to cope.

391
00:36:36,710 --> 00:36:39,070
I haven't met anyone else who can see.

392
00:36:41,550 --> 00:36:43,030
Oh.

393
00:36:45,310 --> 00:36:49,780
In the sideboard, there's the remains
of a bottle of whisky.

394
00:36:49,950 --> 00:36:53,150
I couldn't half do with one. You have one too.

395
00:36:54,510 --> 00:36:58,190
- What's your name?
- Er, Bill.

396
00:36:59,230 --> 00:37:02,110
Why were your eyes bandaged up?

397
00:37:02,270 --> 00:37:07,750
Er, I work on a triffid farm. I got stung by one.

398
00:37:09,470 --> 00:37:12,150
- I nearly went blind.
- Oh.

399
00:37:14,390 --> 00:37:15,790
Here.

400
00:37:15,950 --> 00:37:17,350
There.

401
00:37:18,630 --> 00:37:23,310
- Are there people on the streets?
- No, it's eerie. It's almost totally quiet.

402
00:37:23,470 --> 00:37:25,780
- That won't last.
- What do you mean?

403
00:37:25,950 --> 00:37:28,020
Ta.

404
00:37:28,190 --> 00:37:31,550
Well, everybody will be like us at first.

405
00:37:31,710 --> 00:37:36,830
They won't know what's happened.
They'll be too frightened to move.

406
00:37:36,990 --> 00:37:40,300
Then they'll get hungry and start looking for food.

407
00:37:41,310 --> 00:37:48,310
In two or three days, it won't be just hooligans
killing each other for scraps of food.

408
00:37:53,230 --> 00:37:56,670
I'm sorry. That's, um... That's stupid.

409
00:37:59,230 --> 00:38:01,510
Give us another one.

410
00:38:02,990 --> 00:38:06,870
No, those comet lights came nearest to here.

411
00:38:07,030 --> 00:38:09,750
Everyone else should be all right.

412
00:38:10,710 --> 00:38:15,500
Before you know where you are,
there'll be Red Cross, Sally Army,

413
00:38:15,670 --> 00:38:18,900
Royal Marines pouring in, and doctors, too.

414
00:38:19,790 --> 00:38:23,710
There's hundreds of cases of people
going temporarily blind.

415
00:38:23,870 --> 00:38:26,430
It's a question of proper treatment.

416
00:38:26,590 --> 00:38:29,870
Be best if you stop with us for the time being.

417
00:38:30,030 --> 00:38:31,510
Why?

418
00:38:31,670 --> 00:38:37,030
It would be best, wouldn't it?
Two who can see, and two who are blind.

419
00:38:37,190 --> 00:38:39,710
We can manage like that.

420
00:38:39,870 --> 00:38:43,990
We'll give you shelter and you give us help.

421
00:38:44,150 --> 00:38:47,300
That would be best, don't you think?

422
00:38:48,150 --> 00:38:51,350
- What about the others?
- What others?

423
00:38:51,510 --> 00:38:55,630
Your child can see.
The others have no one. What about them?

424
00:38:55,790 --> 00:38:59,100
What about them? Can you help all of them?

425
00:38:59,270 --> 00:39:02,950
Which are you gonna pick? The first you meet?

426
00:39:03,110 --> 00:39:09,060
The 20th? The 2,645th?
Talk sense, for God's sake!

427
00:39:10,550 --> 00:39:13,390
There's not just us in this flat.

428
00:39:14,310 --> 00:39:17,270
There's the rest of the block.

429
00:39:17,430 --> 00:39:19,820
You could manage all of them.

430
00:39:21,670 --> 00:39:24,510
That's enough, isn't it?

431
00:39:25,150 --> 00:39:28,110
Don't leave us...please.

432
00:39:31,670 --> 00:39:36,140
There's got to be others who can see.
Tina can see. I can see.

433
00:39:36,310 --> 00:39:41,340
There's got to be others. We can organise
something till the real help comes.

434
00:39:41,510 --> 00:39:46,830
There's nothing and there's no one.
Haven't you got that yet?

435
00:39:46,990 --> 00:39:49,190
I've got to try and find out!

436
00:39:50,550 --> 00:39:55,580
Look, you'll be all right.
You've got Tina. You'll be all right!

437
00:39:56,830 --> 00:39:59,750
There's nothing you'll be able to do.

438
00:39:59,910 --> 00:40:03,700
When you realise that, you come back.

439
00:40:03,870 --> 00:40:05,590
If you're still alive then.

